header.gameNote: ATLANTIC SUN MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - SEMIFINALS AT MACON GA

article.headline: North Florida 59, ETSU 55
article.story: MACON, Ga. -- David Jeune recorded his second career double-double with 13 points and 11 rebounds as sixth-seeded North Florida upset second-seeded East Tennessee State 59-55 on Friday in the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament semifinals. North Florida (15-18) faces top-seeded Belmont at 6 p.m. on Saturday in the championship. The Ospreys had never defeated ETSU, the two-time defending tournament champion, until Friday. Conference player of the year Mike Smith led ETSU (22-11) with 20 points. Leading 57-55, North Florida got the stop it needed when ETSU's Adam Sollazzo missed a layup, and Jeune grabbed the rebound with 14 seconds left. Jeune was fouled and made both free throws to clinch the win. For the second straight year, the No. 6 seed has advanced to the final. A sixth seed has won the title only once -- 1996, when Central Florida defeated Mercer.
